org.opends.guitools.controlpanel.util

Class LDAPEntryReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opends.guitools.controlpanel.util.BackgroundTask<Entry>
      • org.opends.guitools.controlpanel.util.LDAPEntryReader

  • public class LDAPEntryReader
extends BackgroundTask<Entry>
    A class that reads an entry on the background. This is used in the LDAP entries browser. When the entry is read it notifies to the EntryReadListener objects that have been registered.

      • backgroundTaskCompleted

        public void backgroundTaskCompleted(Entry sr,
                                    Throwable throwable)
        Description copied from class: BackgroundTask
        This method will be invoked to indicate that the background task has completed. If processing completed successfully, then the Throwable argument will be null and the returnValue argument will contain the value returned by the processBackgroundTask method. If an exception or error was thrown, then the throwable argument will not be null.
        Specified by:
        backgroundTaskCompleted in class BackgroundTask<Entry>
        Parameters:
        sr - The value returned by the processBackgroundTask method when processing completed, or null if no value was returned or an exception was encountered during processing.
        throwable - A Throwable instance (e.g., an exception) that was raised during processing, or null if all processing completed successfully.
